But, over the weekend, Democratic presidential candidate Beto O’Rourke apologized for for writings he made as a teenager describing fantasies about running over children with a vehicle.
Here’s more:“I’m mortified to read it now, incredibly embarrassed, but I have to take ownership of my words,” the Democratic presidential candidate said during a taping of the “Political Party Live” podcast in Cedar Rapids, Iowa.
“It’s not anything I’m proud of today, and I mean, that’s — that’s the long and short of it,” he said.
The news is perhaps not surprising given that O’Rourke supports abortions up to birth.
